A politician, Eniola Adeyemi, aka Wake Up, has said bills that will improve the creative industry, waterways, and health sector, among others, need to be sponsored to impact the lives of residents in Lagos State. Adeyemi, who is vying for a seat in the Lagos State House of Assembly in Ikorodu Constituency 1, said he was bent on sponsoring such bills to improve the welfare of residents and create avenues to appreciate talented individuals in the state. He said, “The world is evolving; science is changing a lot of things; cultures are becoming outdated; arts are becoming obsolete. Ours, as a new generation, is to assist our society and humanity, in general, to recreate and evolve modern approaches to social, economic, political, and other engagements for maximum outputs that would benefit all. “That is why we must stand up to become that change agent, especially in the political arena. We shall do this with the responsibility to join others in building a peaceful society that will rest on the principles  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com